cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.DC 

This paper focuses on evaluating the performance of next-generation networks for vehicular safety applications, which involves networking, communication, and system aspects. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also deals with security and reliability issues, which fall under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of SDN and NFV technologies also involves system-level design and optimization, which could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the delay and energy consumption aspects, which could be related to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
